_refine_special_details          
;
 Refinement of F^2^ against ALL reflections.  The weighted R-factor wR and 
 goodness of fit S are based on F^2^, conventional R-factors R are based 
 on F, with F set to zero for negative F^2^. The threshold expression of 
 F^2^ > 2sigma(F^2^) is used only for calculating R-factors(gt) etc. and is 
 not relevant to the choice of reflections for refinement.  R-factors based 
 on F^2^ are statistically about twice as large as those based on F, and R- 
 factors based on ALL data will be even larger.  All non-H atoms, including 
 the organic cations and disorder Pb2I7 fragments were located in 
 difference-Fourier maps, and then refined anisotropically. The restraints 
 on bond lengths of the atomic displacement parameters of organic cations 
 (DFIX/SADI instructions of SHELXL-2014), as well as the constraints or 
 restraints of the atomic displacement parameters (RIGU or SIMU/ISOR 
 instructions of SHELXL-2014) if necessary, have been applied for the organic 
 cations refinement. 

 There is limitation for using X-ray single crystal diffraction to determine 
 the geometry of small organic cation in a heavy element inorganic framework.
 Also, the crystal quality became worse due to the phase change and/or X-ray 
 damage. The Pb2I7 fragment is refined as two-components disorder although 
 there maybe another disoder Pb2I7 fragment (< 5%) in the stucture. The 
 disorder organic cations (< 10%) haven't been modeled.  
;

